SECOND REGULAR SESSION
SENATE BILL NO. 1734
103RD GENERA L ASSEMBLY
INTRODUCED BY SENATOR GREGORY (15).
7353S.01I KRISTINA MARTIN, Secretary
AN ACT
To amend chapter 311, RSMo, by adding thereto one new section relating to the establishment of
certain entertainment districts.
Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the State of Missouri, as follows:
1 Section A. Chapter 311, RSMo, is amended by adding thereto
2 one new section, to be known as section 311.083, to read as
3 follows:
1 311.083. 1. As used in this section, the following
2 terms mean:
3 (1) "Common area", any public area within an
4 entertainment district and any area of a public right-of-way
5 that is within the entertainment district. "Common area"
6 shall not include areas open to the public that are located
7 within an establishment licensed under this chapter;
8 (2) "Entertainment district", any area in any county
9 bordering the Missouri river, and that:
10 (a) Is located in any city with more than forty-six
11 thousand but fewer than fifty-one thousand inhabitants;
12 (b) Contains a combination of entertainment venues,
13 bars, nightclubs, restaurants, and other licensed
14 establishments and common areas; and
15 (c) Is designated as such by an ordinance of the
16 governing body of the city;

SB 1734 2
17 (3) "Portable bar", any bar, table, kiosk, cart, or
18 stand that is not a permanent fixture and can be moved from
19 place to place.
20 2. Notwithstanding any other provisions of this
21 chapter to the contrary, any person who possesses the
22 qualifications required under this chapter, and who meets
23 the requirements of and complies with the provisions of this
24 chapter, may apply for, and the supervisor of alcohol and
25 tobacco control may issue, an entertainment district special
26 license to sell intoxicating liquor by the drink for retail
27 for consumption dispensed from one or more licensed
28 establishments including, but not limited to, portable bars
29 within the entertainment district, until 1:30 a.m. on
30 Mondays through Saturdays and from 6:00 a.m. on Sundays and
31 until 1:30 a.m. on Mondays.
32 3. An applicant granted an entertainment district
33 special license under this section shall pay a license fee
34 of three hundred dollars per year.
35 4. Notwithstanding any other provision of this chapter
36 to the contrary, on such days and at such times during the
37 hours a licensee is allowed under this chapter to sell
38 alcoholic beverages, licensed establishments holding an
39 entertainment district special license under this section
40 may allow persons to leave the licensed premises located in
41 portions of the entertainment district with an alcoholic
42 beverage and enter upon and consume the alcoholic beverage
43 within other licensed establishments and common areas
44 located in portions of the entertainment district. No
45 person shall take any alcoholic beverage or alcoholic
46 beverages outside the boundaries of the entertainment
47 district.

SB 1734 3
48 5. Every licensee within the entertainment district
49 shall serve alcoholic beverages in containers that display
50 and contain the licensee's trade name or logo or some other
51 mark that is unique to that license and licensee.
52 6. The holder of an entertainment district special
53 license is solely responsible for alcohol violations
54 occurring on its premises, including any portable bar, and
55 in any common area.
56 7. The governing body of the city in which the
57 entertainment district is located shall be authorized to
58 adopt by ordinance procedures for approval or rejection of
59 such entertainment districts as well as rules and
60 regulations for conduct and enforcement thereof consistent
61 with this section.
